28:44.769 --> 28:49.436
Yeah. You might as well just kill
yourself now. I can sort the drugs.

28:50.574 --> 28:51.747
Look.

28:51.847 --> 28:56.312
There's loads of people out there that want
a kid that can't have one. Give it away.

28:58.648 --> 29:01.149
I could still move to Boston.

29:01.920 --> 29:05.123
I can apply to college again,
or get a job. I don't care.

29:05.223 --> 29:07.459
So it would all be the same,
just six months later. I mean,

29:07.559 --> 29:09.995
I don't even need to tell Alex,
I could just think of an excuse.

29:10.095 --> 29:12.729
Whoa. That's major denial, babe.

29:12.931 --> 29:14.432
Yeah.

29:14.532 --> 29:17.365
I just happen to think
it's the way to go.

29:26.845 --> 29:28.713
- Who's that?
- Alex.

29:28.813 --> 29:30.048
Have you told him yet?

29:30.148 --> 29:33.284
I'm sending him my arrival time in Boston.
That's all he needs to know.

29:33.384 --> 29:36.318
All this fibbing is gonna
catch up with you, girl.

29:38.923 --> 29:41.390
The way that thing burst out of her.

29:41.859 --> 29:43.867
- That might happen to you!
- It might.

29:44.694 --> 29:47.766
Her whole belly will erupt.
Blood and guts.

29:47.866 --> 29:51.136
And this freakish alien will
leap out and bite your head off!

29:51.636 --> 29:54.873
Stop it, the pair of you!
Pregnancy is a sacred thing!

29:55.073 --> 29:57.041
- It can't hear us.
- Yes, it can!

29:57.141 --> 30:00.411
- And don't refer to it as "it."
- It's a girl if you must know.

30:00.590 --> 30:02.400
You found out?

30:02.500 --> 30:04.383
I asked at the last scan.

30:04.483 --> 30:07.049
I thought I should tell the social worker
so he can start his plans.

30:07.651 --> 30:09.607
A girl!

30:10.221 --> 30:14.556
- What about names?
- No, I'll let the new parents decide.

30:15.358 --> 30:16.662
- Give us a peek.
- Hey!

30:16.823 --> 30:20.498
A woman's body doesn't become public property
just because she is pregnant, you know.

30:20.598 --> 30:21.730
Be my guest.

30:26.970 --> 30:29.187
Look at that!

30:30.107 --> 30:33.084
Oh, my God!

30:34.211 --> 30:36.281
She's got hiccups!

30:36.670 --> 30:38.213
The little thing's got hiccups!

30:38.949 --> 30:41.339
Oh, bless!

30:42.719 --> 30:44.525
Whatever.

30:56.433 --> 30:58.900
Baby, can you hear me?

31:03.841 --> 31:07.975
Try holding your breath like this.

31:15.919 --> 31:18.553
There you are, Katie girl!

31:22.659 --> 31:27.128
That's probably not going to
be your name, okay?

31:33.670 --> 31:36.574
It's coming! Towels! Hot water!

31:36.674 --> 31:39.241
- Where's the midwife?
- I don't know!

31:40.463 --> 31:42.878
Come in now! Come on!

31:43.246 --> 31:44.883
- Come on!
- Midwife's here!

31:44.983 --> 31:48.850
Let's go! As quick as you like!
She's just right down the hallway.

31:49.621 --> 31:52.754
- All right, okay, breathe, breathe!
- Get out!

31:53.859 --> 31:56.527
Breathe, everything is
going to be all right!

31:56.627 --> 31:59.127
- Being a girl sucks!
- Yeah.

32:03.201 --> 32:05.325
Hello.

32:07.671 --> 32:09.905
That'll be the social worker.

32:11.975 --> 32:14.223
Would you like to hold her?

32:14.579 --> 32:17.252
Or should I bring her
straight downstairs?

32:48.511 --> 32:50.345
Katie.

32:52.349 --> 32:55.013
Sweet little Katie.

33:22.179 --> 33:24.702
I promise, Katie,

33:25.483 --> 33:28.049
I'm going to be a good Mommy.

33:44.156 --> 33:45.893
Katie.

33:46.203 --> 33:48.014
Katie.

33:58.014 --> 34:00.382
It's gonna be okay.

34:02.185 --> 34:06.330
Please. Katie, it's gonna be okay!

34:10.994 --> 34:15.030
- My life's over, Dad!
- Wait 'til you become a grandparent.

34:17.034 --> 34:19.900
Katie, Katie.

34:26.610 --> 34:30.949
You know, I still remember the drive back
from the hospital when you were born.

34:31.049 --> 34:35.241
You screamed blue murder,
the whole bloody journey.

34:36.319 --> 34:38.723
I was so scared,
I jumped three red lights.

34:38.822 --> 34:41.357
- Lost my license.
- You never told me that before.

34:43.126 --> 34:44.359
You weren't part of the club.

34:55.272 --> 34:58.777
<i>In battle to preserve sanity,
must remember following rules.</i>

34:58.877 --> 35:02.344
<i>Number one, never breast feed
in a public place.</i>

35:04.112 --> 35:07.983
<i>Two, never bounce Katie
on knee after feeding.</i>

35:10.020 --> 35:13.220
<i>Three, try not to cry when she cries.</i>

35:13.857 --> 35:16.161
<i>And four, the most important of all,</i>

35:16.261 --> 35:19.327
<i>never assume trouble
isn't around the next corner.</i>

35:19.596 --> 35:22.409
- Laters, girls.
- Bye.

35:42.852 --> 35:44.695
Rosie? Oh, no.

35:44.895 --> 35:48.356
Tragic. Are you okay?

35:50.161 --> 35:53.762
- Tell me that's not yours!
- No!

35:55.098 --> 35:56.735
What, you're a nanny now?

35:56.935 --> 35:59.712
Yeah! You know,
at least it's good money.

36:00.438 --> 36:02.337
I thought you were
going to Boston with Alex.

36:03.206 --> 36:07.311
Oh, no, no, no, I realized children
are the only education you need.

36:08.304 --> 36:10.212
So, who's the dad?

36:13.684 --> 36:15.317
Get it off! Get it off!

36:17.154 --> 36:20.088
- I've got to go!
- Bye, then!

36:38.775 --> 36:40.638
Alex.

36:41.511 --> 36:42.847
What are you doing here?

36:43.047 --> 36:45.617
Just back for the weekend.
Thought I'd surprise you.

36:45.917 --> 36:49.320
Great! Yeah. Let's go for a coffee then.

36:49.420 --> 36:52.754
No, no. Let's stay here.
Why don't you put the kettle on?

37:01.899 --> 37:05.069
- So, what have you been up to?
- Oh, just this and that, you know?

37:05.169 --> 37:07.939
- Nice haircut by the way.
- Yeah, thanks.

37:08.039 --> 37:11.306
- You okay? You seem stressed.
- No! No!

37:11.941 --> 37:13.843
So, how's medicine?

37:13.943 --> 37:16.110
Fascinating. Yeah.

37:16.780 --> 37:18.482
We've just been
doing obstetrics, in fact.

37:18.582 --> 37:20.239
Really?

37:21.484 --> 37:24.488
So much to learn. How do you find
these breast pumps, by the way?

37:24.588 --> 37:27.955
- Some women don't like them.
- Oh, total nightmare.

37:30.159 --> 37:31.828
Oh, God.

37:32.228 --> 37:33.678
How did you...

37:33.778 --> 37:35.263
Bethany.

37:36.766 --> 37:38.500
Fast work.

37:42.605 --> 37:45.015
I was gonna tell you, Alex, I promise.

37:45.115 --> 37:46.665
When?

37:47.544 --> 37:50.945
I didn't want to hold you back.

37:54.417 --> 37:56.954
She's had colic for months.

37:57.054 --> 38:00.989
My whole life is feeding,
winding and nappies.

38:02.259 --> 38:04.607
All I can think about is poo.

38:05.061 --> 38:07.229
How much, when, what color.

38:08.465 --> 38:09.731
I hope you mean hers.

38:16.939 --> 38:19.006
What happened to Greg?

38:19.109 --> 38:23.178
He miraculously got a job
in Ibiza the minute he heard.

38:33.289 --> 38:34.939
Can I be godfather?

38:39.162 --> 38:41.529
I'd love nothing more.

38:55.278 --> 38:58.546
I think not telling you

38:58.648 --> 39:01.016
was a way to keep
the dream alive, you know?

39:03.386 --> 39:08.323
So there was at least someone
out there who still saw me as Rosie.

39:09.659 --> 39:14.562
And not this strange,
new person I've become.

40:26.403 --> 40:28.347
So...

40:28.447 --> 40:32.641
the last time I looked that depressed,
I tried to hang myself with my favorite tie.

40:36.245 --> 40:38.680
Hi, I'm Phil.

40:40.083 --> 40:41.321
Alex.

40:41.421 --> 40:44.316
I've been sent to play fairy godmother.

40:45.388 --> 40:47.122
You don't look the part, mate.

40:48.291 --> 40:52.460
My sister's been driving me crazy.
She wants to know, would you buy her a drink?

40:54.163 --> 40:55.953
Which one is she?

41:01.404 --> 41:03.282
The hot girl from class?

41:03.382 --> 41:07.742
Sally. The bright sunflower
in the family window box.

41:09.879 --> 41:12.050
- Hey!
- Hey!

41:12.150 --> 41:15.917
Everybody has been wondering
why the cute British guy looks so sad.

41:17.386 --> 41:18.973
Sorry.

41:19.589 --> 41:22.526
It's time to realize
you're here with us.

41:22.626 --> 41:25.760
And that we might be fun to be with.

41:31.034 --> 41:33.270
Katie! It's your first Christmas!

41:33.770 --> 41:35.206
I hope you got my present!

41:35.406 --> 41:37.775
<i>Thanks for the book, Alex.
I know she'll love it...</i>

41:38.175 --> 41:39.310
- <i>...one day.</i>
- What is it?

41:39.410 --> 41:42.076
This is my new apartment.

41:42.579 --> 41:44.281
What's this you're doing here, darling?

41:45.040 --> 41:46.317
Handmade hearts.

41:46.417 --> 41:49.119
And here, we have my favorite
<i>Back to the Future</i> poster.

41:49.219 --> 41:51.722
It would look so special
in the bathroom.

41:51.922 --> 41:53.188
Walk to Mommy.

41:53.456 --> 41:55.626
- Come to me.
- Good girl!

41:55.726 --> 41:58.960
Katie, darling,
it's your fourth Christmas.

42:00.997 --> 42:03.164
<i>Did, Mommy get my Christmas card?</i>

42:08.437 --> 42:09.473
Really?

42:09.573 --> 42:14.511
<i>Thanks for Katie's present. She wants me
to tell you she can cycle and count to five.</i>

42:14.611 --> 42:18.078
...three, four, five!

42:18.448 --> 42:22.520
<i>Me, I've got a job and finally
moved out of Mom and Dad's.</i>

42:22.620 --> 42:25.323
Miss Dunne! Welcome back to the hotel!

42:25.423 --> 42:27.525
I believe it's the
penthouse suite for you?

42:27.625 --> 42:29.757
That's right, thanks.

43:15.137 --> 43:18.005
Mommy, Mommy!
It's the first day of school!

43:21.611 --> 43:24.348
I heard some beds

43:24.448 --> 43:26.784
were being stolen recently.

43:26.884 --> 43:29.387
- Isn't that strange?
- Yes, Mommy.

43:29.487 --> 43:32.620
This way, no one can
come in and steal ours.

43:35.524 --> 43:37.058
Are you my daddy?

43:37.760 --> 43:41.796
No! No, he's just a nice man that's
helping Mommy out a bit, that's all.

43:46.036 --> 43:47.071
- Damn!
- What?

43:47.171 --> 43:49.103
It's the wrong key!

44:00.751 --> 44:02.317
- My head!
- Come on, whinger!

44:05.354 --> 44:06.990
Over there! Over there!

44:07.090 --> 44:09.626
- Come on, keep going.
- Quick, quick, Mommy!

44:09.826 --> 44:11.459
Excuse me.

44:14.363 --> 44:17.235
- Love you.
- Love you, too.

44:23.272 --> 44:25.443
You dreamt you were an inanimate object?

44:25.543 --> 44:29.947
Yeah, I mean, come on. An arrow flying
through the air! That's pretty cool.

44:30.347 --> 44:33.584
I don't understand.
How can you be a thing?

44:33.684 --> 44:36.387
I don't know.
I've always had dreams like that.

44:37.287 --> 44:39.721
It sounds to me like
self-esteem issues, sweetie.

44:40.256 --> 44:41.870
You may need to talk to someone.

44:45.128 --> 44:49.032
You know, there are razor hairs
in the bathroom, again today.

44:49.132 --> 44:52.503
- Really?
- You know it gives me allergies.

44:52.803 --> 44:55.205
Next time you have
one of your weird dreams,

44:55.305 --> 45:01.208
maybe you should dream you're
something useful like a vacuum cleaner.

45:01.811 --> 45:05.049
- We have a cleaning lady.
- What do you want?

45:05.149 --> 45:07.782
For her to think
we're a pair of fuck-ups?

45:08.117 --> 45:10.219
That's exactly what we are.

45:24.634 --> 45:27.283
- You okay?
- I've got sand in my eyes.

45:28.271 --> 45:30.405
Look at Mommy!

45:38.715 --> 45:40.782
<i>I dreamt I was an arrow.</i>

45:41.382 --> 45:45.431
<i>The little metal bit right at the tip of
an arrow, whizzing through the air.</i>

46:10.479 --> 46:12.658
What have you told the poor brat?
Are you coming home for dad?

46:12.758 --> 46:15.886
No! Just that he sent me a ticket.
I've got no expectations.

46:15.986 --> 46:17.888
Well, good,
because he's got a girlfriend.

46:17.988 --> 46:20.491
Although you know it's funny,
her name didn't come up once.

46:20.591 --> 46:24.394
Yeah, well, Katie's mature enough to know
that when it comes to men, it doesn't matter.

46:24.494 --> 46:26.731
Yeah, well, Katie also knows
that something must have triggered

46:26.831 --> 46:29.115
his sudden enthusiasm to see
her mom, who, by the way,

46:29.215 --> 46:32.634
knows him better than anyone,
and is clearly the best person to judge!

46:33.469 --> 46:35.102
Oh, and...

46:57.853 --> 47:00.962
All right! Good to see you!

47:02.364 --> 47:06.656
- So, tired? Hungry?
- No. Why?

47:23.419 --> 47:25.252
Come on.

47:27.323 --> 47:29.002
Do you want another?

47:29.725 --> 47:32.359
- Yeah.
- All right. I'll be back, okay?

47:35.056 --> 47:37.751
So, you're new here.

47:38.376 --> 47:41.138
- I'm Jonathan.
- Rosie.

47:41.238 --> 47:44.173
Rosie? So what do you do, Rosie?

47:44.573 --> 47:45.743
I'm a mom!

47:46.043 --> 47:50.845
Is that some kind of, performance thing?
You're a drama major?

47:51.714 --> 47:54.715
I'm a mother of a 5-year-old girl!

47:55.584 --> 47:58.052
Cool! Cool!

47:59.656 --> 48:04.325
Can I get you a drink or something?

48:06.429 --> 48:08.195
A gin and tonic.

48:09.265 --> 48:11.435
- Cell? Car keys?
- Oh, dude. Come on.

48:11.535 --> 48:14.117
- Guys, guys, guys, no, no, no!
- It's happening.

48:14.218 --> 48:15.939
- It's gonna happen!
- Come on, come on! Come on! Please!

48:16.039 --> 48:19.040
- One, two, three!
- Okay, okay! Rosie, Rosie, come on...

48:27.821 --> 48:31.152
- Give me a hand.
- All right.

48:34.824 --> 48:37.091
Come on. Come on! I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

48:40.164 --> 48:42.130
You're looking way too hot
right now, Rosie.

48:48.571 --> 48:51.740
Come on, all right, okay.
If you want it like that.

48:51.840 --> 48:53.508
No, no, no!

49:01.385 --> 49:02.984
Bananas?

49:07.690 --> 49:09.557
- Any good?
- No, it's sort of...

49:12.928 --> 49:14.429
Catch.

49:15.831 --> 49:17.364
All right.

49:18.935 --> 49:21.976
"You will live a long and happy life."

49:22.076 --> 49:23.371
- Sweet.
- Oh, can I switch?

49:24.407 --> 49:26.110
- 'Cause you prefer mine?
- I prefer it.

49:26.410 --> 49:30.244
I do, I do. I don't know
what I'm talking about.

49:30.913 --> 49:33.948
Well, you do go here, so you probably
should know what you're talking about.

49:40.723 --> 49:44.258
<i>Strange to think that I could have
lived here and been part of it.</i>

49:45.428 --> 49:48.796
But I don't regret Katie, you know?

49:49.531 --> 49:52.285
I mean, how could I?

49:52.635 --> 49:56.611
She's... she's the most amazing kid.

50:01.777 --> 50:04.311
The weird thing is that...

50:05.982 --> 50:09.116
she reminds me more of you than Greg.

50:10.352 --> 50:13.053
That's probably just 'cause I love her.

50:29.404 --> 50:30.538
We should go.

50:32.574 --> 50:34.426
Yeah.

50:35.378 --> 50:37.014
Seriously cute.

50:37.114 --> 50:39.316
It was a ball of fluff.

50:39.824 --> 50:42.087
No seriously.

50:44.353 --> 50:48.190
Sally. Rosie. Rosie, Sally.

50:48.290 --> 50:50.159
Good morning.

50:50.259 --> 50:51.704
Hi.

50:57.766 --> 51:01.772
- Wow. This should be in a museum.
- Oh, it's nothing.

51:01.872 --> 51:05.960
Just quail egg and asparagus in filo pastry
with a cream of rocket sauce.

51:06.876 --> 51:09.340
Well, my regular is baked beans.

51:10.881 --> 51:14.315
Good old British baked bean.
Zero nutritional value.

51:14.850 --> 51:17.251
Yeah. But good on toast.

51:18.588 --> 51:20.522
Oh, you know I can't drink.

51:20.622 --> 51:24.859
Of course. But how are we going to cope
without the numbing haze of alcohol?

51:26.462 --> 51:30.431
Why can't you drink?
If that's not a rude question?

51:33.602 --> 51:35.271
Alex?

51:37.539 --> 51:38.969
What?

51:49.019 --> 51:50.854
Didn't... Didn't...

51:50.954 --> 51:53.187
Alex and I are pregnant.

51:53.622 --> 51:56.115
Twelve and a half weeks in.

51:59.561 --> 52:01.495
That's wonderful.

52:02.699 --> 52:06.233
Congratulations. Congratulations.

52:07.303 --> 52:11.708
- Alex, you didn't tell me?
- No, I... Sorry, I thought I did.

52:12.108 --> 52:13.774
That's...

52:15.310 --> 52:17.481
Let me help! Shit!

52:17.581 --> 52:19.246
Daddy's antique table! Alex, quick!

52:19.982 --> 52:21.719
- Oh, bollocks.
- Language, please!

52:22.119 --> 52:25.686
- Oh, fuck!
- No! Why can't you just say fudge?

52:40.502 --> 52:43.079
Look what you made me do.

52:45.608 --> 52:48.512
It's fine. It's okay.

52:48.612 --> 52:52.516
We have Herb's vernissage
in an hour... It's...

52:52.616 --> 52:55.282
Everything is gonna be fine.

53:11.967 --> 53:14.134
I'm so sorry.

53:15.071 --> 53:18.842
Sally had this planned for weeks.
It's not for long, okay? I promise.

53:18.942 --> 53:22.045
Sweetie? Dr. Jones is by the
sweet and sour prawn balls!

53:22.145 --> 53:24.915
- He's just...
- Sweetie, not now. Okay?

53:25.015 --> 53:28.151
But he's a senior
thoracic surgeon, Alex.

53:28.251 --> 53:30.953
She's right, Alex. Go on.

53:31.053 --> 53:32.866
Okay, let's go. Let's go.

53:35.391 --> 53:38.929
This image here is one of my favorites.

53:39.029 --> 53:41.727
How to articulate that transient moment

53:41.827 --> 53:46.802
when you see something
through the camera's eye.

53:46.902 --> 53:51.275
It's a little like love at first sight.
Stops you in your tracks.

53:51.375 --> 53:55.278
Suddenly you recognize it
for exactly what it is.

53:55.378 --> 53:57.135
A load of bollocks.

54:02.686 --> 54:06.256
- Rosie! Rosie, where are you going?
- Back home.

54:06.356 --> 54:08.058
And I mean England.
This is too crazy for me, okay?

54:08.158 --> 54:10.060
I walked straight into the middle
of something here!

54:10.160 --> 54:14.598
Look, it's all fine, honestly.
Sally and I just needed to air some stuff!

54:14.698 --> 54:16.564
Oh, good, I'm glad you're fine,
'cause I'm not!

54:17.399 --> 54:19.569
We were out together
the whole night, Alex!

54:19.669 --> 54:23.689
And all the while your girlfriend was at home
expecting a baby! And you didn't say!

54:23.789 --> 54:27.044
Come on, Rosie. Nothing happened,
we were just... We were just having some fun.

54:27.144 --> 54:30.113
That's what you got me
over here for then? Just some fun?

54:30.213 --> 54:33.250
I wanted to see you!
For Christ sake, you're my best friend!

54:33.350 --> 54:37.985
Or maybe you needed someone
from your old life to point out the truth!

54:40.522 --> 54:42.826
- What truth?
- You're in a mess, Alex!

54:42.926 --> 54:46.096
This whole situation
is one big bloody giant mess!

54:46.196 --> 54:47.364
Me? I'm in a mess?

54:47.464 --> 54:49.873
- And you're in denial!
- You're projecting!

54:49.973 --> 54:52.369
Okay, can we just stop
the psychobabble here

54:52.469 --> 54:54.704
and just talk like
English people, please!

54:54.804 --> 54:57.041
Fine! Fine! Fine. Fine. Look.

54:57.341 --> 55:01.445
I was worried you might find it hard,
you know, coming here.

55:01.745 --> 55:05.378
- Hard?
- I mean, you've had a tough time, Rosie, and...

55:05.814 --> 55:10.319
seeing where we live, you know,
our apartment, our lifestyle, it's just...

55:10.494 --> 55:13.657
You thought I was jealous of you? No.

55:13.757 --> 55:15.548
I pity you, Alex!

55:16.162 --> 55:19.229
All I see is someone compensating
for a crap personal life

55:19.329 --> 55:22.433
- by schmoozing his way up the career ladder!
- Crap personal life?

55:22.633 --> 55:26.268
All right, let's see. Stable relationship
with beautiful girlfriend,

55:26.368 --> 55:29.287
lots in common, a great circle
of friends, a kid on the way,

55:29.387 --> 55:31.500
who's gonna have two parents,
by the way, not one!

55:40.816 --> 55:43.650
- Rosie, come on, I...
