<i>At a church where people're saying</i>

56:45.625 --> 56:48.283
<i>"My God that's tough, she stood him up!</i>

56:48.383 --> 56:51.401
<i>No point in us remaining.</i>

56:51.501 --> 56:53.931
<i>May as well go home."</i>

56:54.031 --> 56:56.703
<i>As I did on my own</i>

56:56.803 --> 57:00.967
<i>Alone again, naturally</i>

57:02.319 --> 57:07.046
<i>It seems to me that there are
more hearts broken in the world</i>

57:07.146 --> 57:12.631
<i>That can't be mended, left unattended</i>

57:12.731 --> 57:15.080
<i>What do we do?</i>

57:15.530 --> 57:17.901
<i>What do we do?</i>

57:24.692 --> 57:27.432
<i>Alone again</i>

57:27.532 --> 57:29.908
<i>Naturally</i>

57:42.404 --> 57:43.941
Oh, no!

57:44.973 --> 57:46.440
Pleased to see me?

57:47.042 --> 57:48.111
What are you doing here?

57:48.211 --> 57:50.781
You sent me Katie's drawing!
I got on the first flight I could!

57:51.181 --> 57:54.117
No! No, no, no!
I did that on a whim, okay?

57:54.217 --> 57:57.420
Katie drew the picture, and it was a mistake!
I never expected you to actually show up!

57:57.520 --> 58:01.657
That letter really made me think about my life!
I wanna meet her, Rosie! I am her dad.

58:02.257 --> 58:03.802
Dad?

58:04.293 --> 58:07.328
And what precisely is it that you think
qualifies you for that title? Those?

58:08.364 --> 58:12.002
Where were you, "Dad" when she woke up with
colic every night for the first few months?

58:12.102 --> 58:15.771
Or cut her first tooth,
or took her first steps?

58:16.173 --> 58:18.672
Has anyone ever told you,
you have the most amazing eyes?

58:26.448 --> 58:30.687
Look, I'm sorry, okay? I get it,
I bailed on you. I was a total creep.

58:30.787 --> 58:32.822
But there hasn't been a single day
in the last five years

58:32.922 --> 58:34.691
that I haven't wondered what she's like.

58:34.791 --> 58:38.027
Is she like me?
Did she luck out on the gene front?

58:38.127 --> 58:39.709
You're so full of shit!

58:46.101 --> 58:49.973
You have to give me a chance, Rosie!
I can be different, I promise.

58:50.373 --> 58:53.243
Do you want me to crawl on my hands and knees?
Anything, Rosie! I'm begging you!

58:53.343 --> 58:56.913
Get up, you idiot. If this were about me,
I'd be driving you to the airport right now!

58:57.013 --> 58:59.215
You'd be right to.

59:01.583 --> 59:03.602
One chance!

59:04.687 --> 59:06.823
One chance,
but any mess-ups and you're out.

59:07.023 --> 59:09.927
And you be nice! And I don't
just mean average nice, I mean,

59:10.027 --> 59:12.896
Father Christmas-Easter
Bunny-Tom-Hanks-all-rolled-into-one nice!

59:12.996 --> 59:14.698
- Yeah.
- And you will buy her...

59:14.898 --> 59:17.896
the most expensive pair of
shitty pink shoes that you can find!

59:19.768 --> 59:21.935
I'm gonna Google them right now.

59:33.548 --> 59:34.719
- Hi-five!
- Boo!

01:00:09.985 --> 01:00:11.919
Wait a minute. You did what?

01:00:13.621 --> 01:00:18.127
Hey! This is a man who let you
go to casualty on your own

01:00:18.227 --> 01:00:21.064
in the middle of the night,
with a condom stuck up your fanny!

01:00:21.164 --> 01:00:23.300
He's Katie's dad.

01:00:23.400 --> 01:00:26.002
You should see her little face
light up when he walks in the room!

01:00:26.102 --> 01:00:28.118
They're really bonding.

01:00:29.171 --> 01:00:32.042
Of course, none of that would matter
if he had a crap bod.

01:00:32.142 --> 01:00:34.641
He's really worked on that thing. Wow.

01:00:35.377 --> 01:00:37.107
You're evil, Rosie Dunne.

01:00:39.181 --> 01:00:41.818
I just want to belong to someone, Ruby.

01:00:41.918 --> 01:00:44.351
I'm tired of waiting.

01:00:44.453 --> 01:00:46.987
And it feels good with him.

01:00:47.656 --> 01:00:49.423
We're a family.

01:01:20.790 --> 01:01:24.127
- Can you just stop jumping up and down?
- I'm just checking everyone's here.

01:01:24.227 --> 01:01:26.829
Everyone being who, exactly?

01:01:26.929 --> 01:01:29.832
- How's the blushing bride?
- Like a mad bunny.

01:01:29.932 --> 01:01:32.398
Okay. Okay.

01:01:36.171 --> 01:01:39.376
Don't take this
the wrong way, love. But...

01:01:39.476 --> 01:01:44.547
if there's any part of you that
isn't sure, even now, say the word.

01:01:44.647 --> 01:01:46.780
We'll walk straight out of here,
our heads held high.

01:01:47.783 --> 01:01:49.049
So you like Greg, then?

01:01:50.385 --> 01:01:52.753
Come on. Let's get you hitched.

01:03:09.998 --> 01:03:11.188
Do you like this?

01:03:11.500 --> 01:03:14.667
- Katie, would you please?
- Mom!

01:03:15.871 --> 01:03:17.636
Sorry.

01:03:36.091 --> 01:03:38.160
<i>- Hello?</i>
- Sally...

01:03:38.260 --> 01:03:39.794
Rosie.

01:03:41.196 --> 01:03:44.532
- What can I do for you?
- Is Alex there?

01:03:44.832 --> 01:03:46.168
Did he not tell you?

01:03:46.268 --> 01:03:48.905
- <i>Tell me what?</i>
- Alex and I separated.

01:03:49.005 --> 01:03:51.975
- What? When?
- <i>About eight weeks ago?</i>

01:03:52.075 --> 01:03:54.571
Pretty much the day of your wedding.

01:03:59.147 --> 01:04:02.082
- Oh, God!
- <i>What?</i>

01:04:02.951 --> 01:04:05.788
- <i>What?</i>
- I think my water just broke!

01:04:05.888 --> 01:04:09.058
Oh, God! Wait, wait. Are you sure?
Maybe you just wet yourself.

01:04:09.158 --> 01:04:11.494
No, I did not wet myself! Where is Herb?

01:04:11.594 --> 01:04:12.995
- <i>Herb?</i>
- Oh, God.

01:04:13.095 --> 01:04:15.461
<i>- Who, the artist?</i>
- Herb!

01:04:15.830 --> 01:04:17.884
It's happening! The baby!

01:04:18.533 --> 01:04:22.397
It's coming! Herb!

01:05:42.951 --> 01:05:44.184
Katie!

01:05:48.323 --> 01:05:51.127
- Mom! You're supposed to knock!
- The music! It's too loud!

01:05:51.227 --> 01:05:53.793
Can't hear you! The music's too loud!

01:05:54.763 --> 01:05:58.084
- Don't do that!
- Yeah, this music needs to be felt.

01:05:59.401 --> 01:06:01.437
Is that lipstick you're wearing?

01:06:01.537 --> 01:06:04.304
Privacy, Mom! Please!

01:06:05.040 --> 01:06:06.599
Okay!

01:06:08.311 --> 01:06:09.912
Now, have you got the thermal
underwear I gave you?

01:06:10.012 --> 01:06:13.014
- It's the Mediterranean.
- What about cash?

01:06:13.114 --> 01:06:16.631
I've got some extra if you like.
Phone chargers? Your wallet, Dad?

01:06:16.731 --> 01:06:19.087
Rosie, it's fine. Will you stop
fussing like a mother hen?

01:06:19.387 --> 01:06:20.523
Yes.

01:06:20.723 --> 01:06:22.091
- Goodbye!
- Love you.

01:06:22.191 --> 01:06:23.159
- Get in.
- Love you.

01:06:23.359 --> 01:06:24.492
- Bye!
- Bye!

01:06:25.092 --> 01:06:27.126
- Bye.
- Bye.

01:06:29.198 --> 01:06:31.300
<i>So my parents have sold up
and gone backpacking,</i>

01:06:31.400 --> 01:06:34.771
<i>while I get to stay to stay at home
nagging a 12-year-old about lipstick.</i>

01:06:34.971 --> 01:06:39.005
I mean, seriously, could you find
further proof of how fucked up my life is?

01:06:42.710 --> 01:06:43.711
Bethany?

01:06:43.811 --> 01:06:46.773
Rosie Dunne! You work here now?

01:06:47.949 --> 01:06:50.018
I just got promoted to reception.

01:06:50.618 --> 01:06:52.455
Congratulations!

01:06:52.555 --> 01:06:55.291
But you! Your success,
it's... It's amazing!

01:06:55.991 --> 01:06:58.594
I've just flown from Morocco,
tomorrow I fly out again,

01:06:58.694 --> 01:07:00.897
New York, Boston, Chicago, nightmare.

01:07:00.997 --> 01:07:03.132
- The heart bleeds.
- Yeah.

01:07:03.232 --> 01:07:05.766
Boston? You should look up Alex.

01:07:05.866 --> 01:07:09.672
Really? Alex Stewart?
You guys still keep in touch?

01:07:09.872 --> 01:07:12.775
Of course. He could do
with a friendly face.

01:07:12.875 --> 01:07:15.583
Great! I'll get his details
from you later!

01:07:15.877 --> 01:07:17.408
Thanks.

01:07:17.508 --> 01:07:21.045
Could I have some Evian sent up to my room?
It's the only water I can drink.

01:07:21.145 --> 01:07:24.951
Three bottles.
And maid service twice a day?

01:07:25.620 --> 01:07:27.353
Of course.

01:07:30.592 --> 01:07:32.559
That's how fucked-up your life is.

01:07:44.205 --> 01:07:45.244
Mom!

01:07:45.444 --> 01:07:48.908
How is Nice? Have you found
some good places to eat?

01:07:53.949 --> 01:07:56.082
Mom, are you all right?

01:07:57.485 --> 01:07:59.311
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

01:08:00.021 --> 01:08:01.454
<i>I'm...</i>

01:08:05.093 --> 01:08:06.960
Mom, what is it?

01:08:08.296 --> 01:08:10.491
<i>It's bad news for you.</i>

01:08:11.191 --> 01:08:12.599
Mom?

01:08:13.835 --> 01:08:15.969
Mom, what is it?

01:09:13.594 --> 01:09:14.511
Hey.

01:09:16.163 --> 01:09:17.532
Really?

01:09:18.232 --> 01:09:19.843
Yeah.

01:09:25.774 --> 01:09:27.951
When I heard,

01:09:28.711 --> 01:09:31.746
the years fell away, I was...

01:09:31.845 --> 01:09:34.113
I was a fucked-up kid all over again.

01:09:36.518 --> 01:09:39.752
Hero worshipping
this amazing dad you had.

01:09:54.369 --> 01:09:56.144
Sorry.

01:10:01.909 --> 01:10:04.073
I never got to say goodbye.

01:10:04.412 --> 01:10:07.814
Hey, come here. Come here, you. Hey.

01:10:15.923 --> 01:10:19.104
Hey, hey! Hands off my woman!

01:10:22.931 --> 01:10:26.799
I've just been chatting to your cousin.
She is such a bore.

01:10:28.636 --> 01:10:31.904
Seriously? Are you pissed?

01:10:33.908 --> 01:10:36.245
I find funerals really difficult, Alex.

01:10:36.345 --> 01:10:39.048
'cause Rosie, I mean,
she's having a great time.

01:10:39.248 --> 01:10:42.520
- You know what? Fuck you!
- Please.

01:10:43.785 --> 01:10:47.357
Thanks for turning up.
We both really appreciate your support.

01:10:47.822 --> 01:10:49.656
Let's go, come on.

01:11:02.737 --> 01:11:04.370
<i>Rosie,</i>

01:11:05.207 --> 01:11:09.212
<i>you deserve someone who loves you
with every beat of his heart,</i>

01:11:09.612 --> 01:11:13.947
<i>someone who'll always be there for you,
and who'll love every part of you...</i>

01:11:39.007 --> 01:11:41.243
Mom! I'm not going
without my grey skinny jeans!

01:11:41.343 --> 01:11:43.510
All right! I'll get them for you!

01:12:02.230 --> 01:12:05.367
- "Rosie, you deserve someone who..."
- Anything for me?

01:12:05.902 --> 01:12:08.801
Yeah, just this one.

01:12:12.375 --> 01:12:14.155
From Dad.

01:12:14.555 --> 01:12:17.792
- In France, the day before he died.
- Oh, God, don't read that.

01:12:17.892 --> 01:12:20.513
- What?
- Well, it'll upset you.

01:12:22.149 --> 01:12:23.883
I'm already upset.

01:12:24.919 --> 01:12:25.985
Right.

01:12:28.389 --> 01:12:30.481
Do you want me to stay?

01:12:32.427 --> 01:12:34.293
Funnily enough, no.

01:12:35.063 --> 01:12:38.097
Okay. Well, call me if you
need anything, okay?

01:12:51.079 --> 01:12:54.447
<i>Dear Rosie, I can't believe it.</i>

01:12:54.783 --> 01:13:00.052
<i>Here I am at last, finally walking
the Mediterranean coast.</i>

01:13:00.956 --> 01:13:04.527
<i>I've lost count of the years
I've waited for this moment.</i>

01:13:04.627 --> 01:13:06.996
<i>Somehow life got in the way.</i>

01:13:07.096 --> 01:13:10.331
<i>And it was all good,
I don't regret a minute of it,</i>

01:13:10.431 --> 01:13:13.499
<i>but we forget our dreams at our peril.</i>

01:13:13.868 --> 01:13:18.875
<i>I know you had yours, too, and it must feel
sometimes like they're gone for good.</i>

01:13:18.975 --> 01:13:23.042
<i>But I'm so proud of the woman
you've become, Rosie,</i>

01:13:23.344 --> 01:13:25.945
<i>of the mother you've been to Katie.</i>

01:13:26.481 --> 01:13:29.233
<i>What I once said
about you is still true,</i>

01:13:29.333 --> 01:13:33.422
<i>there's nothing you can't do
if you put your mind to it.</i>

01:13:33.522 --> 01:13:37.325
<i>So keep chasing those dreams,
will you, darling?</i>

01:13:37.425 --> 01:13:39.286
<i>For my sake,</i>

01:13:39.642 --> 01:13:41.386
<i>Dad.</i>

01:13:52.307 --> 01:13:56.309
How can someone
just not be there anymore?

01:14:00.114 --> 01:14:01.247
Fuck knows.

01:14:06.888 --> 01:14:11.725
At least he did everything he wanted.
He didn't forget his dreams.

01:14:17.264 --> 01:14:19.765
What if I told you

01:14:19.867 --> 01:14:22.701
I was gonna use my share

01:14:23.004 --> 01:14:27.640
of the money from the house
and get myself a hotel?

01:14:28.309 --> 01:14:30.676
Somewhere simple but...

01:14:31.112 --> 01:14:33.379
But my own place.

01:14:34.315 --> 01:14:37.149
I think that would be awesome, Mom.

01:14:44.359 --> 01:14:48.696
<i>Rosie, I understand that you
haven't been in touch. And...</i>

01:14:48.796 --> 01:14:50.893
<i>I just need to know one thing.</i>

01:14:53.100 --> 01:14:55.229
<i>Are you happy with him?</i>

01:14:58.740 --> 01:15:02.344
<i>There's not much I got right
in my life, but this family,</i>

01:15:02.444 --> 01:15:04.781
<i>somehow we're making it work.</i>

01:15:04.881 --> 01:15:08.363
<i>So I guess the one word answer
to your question should be,</i>

01:15:09.116 --> 01:15:10.683
<i>"Yes."</i>

01:15:18.593 --> 01:15:20.162
- Hey!
- Hi.

01:15:20.262 --> 01:15:22.465
So look at this. The Sweetlands Hotel.

01:15:22.565 --> 01:15:24.611
That's where we had our
end of school dance!

01:15:24.711 --> 01:15:27.770
They just joined our group. I mean,
I was just checking for discounts,

01:15:27.870 --> 01:15:30.369
and I found this booking...

01:15:31.305 --> 01:15:35.811
That's Greg's name!
The bridal suite, for this weekend!

01:15:35.911 --> 01:15:38.314
He's already up there on business.

01:15:38.414 --> 01:15:42.285
Do you think... For our anniversary?

01:15:45.286 --> 01:15:46.896
It's him.

01:15:50.124 --> 01:15:51.293
Hey!

01:15:51.393 --> 01:15:55.864
<i>Hey, gorgeous. Listen, I'm gonna
have to stay here a few extra nights,</i>

01:15:55.964 --> 01:15:58.700
<i>the guys need me to check out
some more venues.</i>

01:15:58.800 --> 01:16:00.391
<i>Can you take Katie and go to your mom's,</i>

01:16:00.491 --> 01:16:03.336
<i>and then I can swing by
on Sunday and pick you up?</i>

01:16:04.772 --> 01:16:06.270
<i>Babe?</i>

01:16:07.274 --> 01:16:08.808
Fine.

01:16:09.010 --> 01:16:11.176
<i>Cool, see you later, then.</i>

01:16:11.412 --> 01:16:13.646
- Talk later.
<i>- Bye.</i>

01:16:17.118 --> 01:16:19.160
Check the booking.

01:16:22.690 --> 01:16:25.088
Here it is. Bridal suite for two,

01:16:25.188 --> 01:16:28.093
checked in two hours ago.

01:16:29.396 --> 01:16:31.364
Oh, Rosie, I'm...

01:16:51.048 --> 01:16:53.419
Rosie? What are you going to say?

01:17:03.030 --> 01:17:04.463
Fuck!

01:18:07.895 --> 01:18:09.513
"Rosie,

01:18:09.932 --> 01:18:13.435
"you deserve someone who loves you
with every beat of his heart.

01:18:13.535 --> 01:18:15.905
"Someone who will always
be there for you,

01:18:16.005 --> 01:18:19.107
"and who will love every part of you,
especially your flaws.

01:18:19.207 --> 01:18:23.753
<i>"I know Katie needs her dad. I don't
want to intrude. So if this is all wrong,</i>

01:18:23.853 --> 01:18:26.912
<i>"just ignore it and I promise
I'll never broach the subject again.</i>

01:18:28.015 --> 01:18:30.650
<i>"Greg's not the man for you, Rosie.</i>

01:18:30.985 --> 01:18:33.225
<i>"Twice I've let you
slip through my fingers.</i>

01:18:33.325 --> 01:18:36.091
<i>"Let's stop being afraid
and take the chance.</i>

01:18:36.191 --> 01:18:40.042
<i>"I know now I can make you happy.
Call me if you feel the same way.</i>

01:18:41.128 --> 01:18:42.862
<i>"Love, Alex."</i>

01:19:28.075 --> 01:19:29.463
Bethany?

01:19:30.244 --> 01:19:33.379
- What are you doing there?
- <i>I live here now. I moved in.</i>

01:19:34.982 --> 01:19:38.385
- <i>Look who it is, Mr. Schnuffs!</i>
- Mr. Schnuffs?

01:19:38.685 --> 01:19:40.319
<i>Rosie?</i>

01:19:49.561 --> 01:19:51.800
<i>Baby, that thing we were
talking about earlier.</i>

01:19:51.900 --> 01:19:53.769
<i>- Yeah.
- Ask her now.</i>

01:19:53.869 --> 01:19:55.380
<i>Schnuffie...</i>

01:19:59.840 --> 01:20:01.707
<i>Bethany and me,</i>

01:20:02.849 --> 01:20:05.180
<i>We thought, why hang around, you know,</i>

01:20:05.280 --> 01:20:08.615
<i>So, she started organizing
the whole thing,</i>

01:20:08.715 --> 01:20:12.485
<i>but then Phil said no,
so your name came up, obviously.</i>

01:20:14.155 --> 01:20:15.921
<i>We're getting married!</i>

01:20:16.992 --> 01:20:19.694
<i>The wedding's next week.
It's fast, but we need to fit it in</i>

01:20:19.794 --> 01:20:23.832
<i>before New York Fashion Week.
And you have to be our best man!</i>

01:20:23.932 --> 01:20:25.835
<i>I mean, you are a girl but... Right?</i>

01:20:25.935 --> 01:20:28.704
<i>This is all because of you, Rosie.
You told me to come here.</i>

01:20:28.804 --> 01:20:32.204
<i>It wouldn't have happened if
it wasn't for you. Thank you.</i>

01:20:36.210 --> 01:20:38.680
It is so great having you as a friend.

01:20:38.780 --> 01:20:41.383
I mean, every time something goes wrong
in my life, all I got to do is look at yours

01:20:41.483 --> 01:20:43.901
and it puts everything into perspective.

01:20:44.051 --> 01:20:46.541
He proposed to her on a boat.

01:20:46.641 --> 01:20:50.292
It's like... It's like Kate and Leonardo
in that scene on the deck.

01:20:50.392 --> 01:20:52.344
The <i>Titanic.</i>

01:20:53.127 --> 01:20:55.178
How appropriate. Look,

01:20:55.278 --> 01:20:58.700
